Opgave 1

1

Givet:

\[ R(s) = \frac{1}{s} \quad G(s)= \frac{10}{s+10}\\ C(s) = R(s)G(s) \]

Derfor:

\[ C(s) = \frac{10}{s(s+10)} = \frac{1}{s} - \frac{1}{s+10} \] Dermed: \[ c(t) = 1 - e^{-10t} \]

\[ \tau = \frac{1}{10}\]

2

Givet:

\[ R(s) = \frac{1}{s} \quad G(s)= \frac{20}{s+15}\\ C(s) = R(s)G(s) \]

Derfor:

\[ C(s) = \frac{20}{s(s+15)} = \frac{\frac{20}{15}}{s} - \frac{\frac{20}{15}}{s+10} \] Dermed: \[ c(t) = \frac{20}{15} \left(1 - e^{-15t}\right) \]

\[ \tau = \frac{1}{15}\]

Opgave 2

Det er en fÃ¸rste ordens funktion, det ses da der intet oversving er, og det er en enklet eksponentiel funktion (Ses pÃ¥ hÃ¦ldning v. \(t=0\))

\[ c_{final} = \frac{3}{4} \] \[ \tau = 0.0016 \quad c(t) = c_{final} \times 0.63 \] \[ a = \frac{1}{\tau} = 625\]

Dermed:

\[ c(t) = 0.75 \left(1-e^{-625t}\right)\]

Det giver: \[ T_v(s) = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\{c(t)\}\\ T_v(s) = \frac{469}{s+625} \]

Opgave 3

Ud fra oversvinget ses det at funktionen er en 2. ordens.

Ud fra grafen aflÃ¦ses \(T\) som vÃ¦rende:

\[ T = t_2 - t_1 \approx 0.0078 - 0.0024 = 5.3 \;\mathrm{ms} \]

Dette giver:

\[ \omega_n = \frac{2\pi}{0.0053} = 1186\; \mathrm{rad/s} \]

\(\tau\) findes ved det punkt hvor kurven er ved \(63\% (63.2\%)\) af \(c_{final}\).

Dette punkt aflÃ¦ses somvÃ¦rende \(\approx 0.0016\). Dette betyder at der vil vÃ¦re en pol i :

\[ p_{1,2} = \frac{1}{\tau} = 625 \; \mathrm{rad/s} \]

Dette vil desuden vÃ¦re konstanten \(a\).

Nu kan \(\zeta\) findes:

\[ \zeta = \frac{a}{2\cdot\omega_n} = \frac{625}{2 \cdot 1186} \]

Hvorfor:

\[ c(t) = 1 - \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-\zeta^2}} e^{-\zeta\omega_n t} \cos\left( \omega_n \sqrt{1-\zeta^2} - \arctan\left(\frac{\zeta}{\sqrt{1-\zeta^2}}\right) \right) \]

A

Vi har:

\[ G(s) = 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s^2+12s+400} \]

\[ C(s) = \frac{1}{s} \cdot 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s^2+12s+400} = 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s(s^2+12s+400)} \]

Her er polparret:

\[ p =-6 \pm 2\sqrt{91} = -6\pm 19.08 \]

Det giver fÃ¸lgende underdÃ¦mpede step respons

\[ c(t) = A + B e^{-\sigma t} + cos(\omega t - \phi) \] Hvor \[ \sigma = 6 \quad \omega = 19.08 \]

AltsÃ¥:

\[ c(t) = A + B e^{-6 t} + cos(19.08 t - \phi) \]

B

\[ G(s) = \frac{900}{s^2+90*s+900} \]

Denne funktion har polerne:

\[ p_1 = -11.46 \quad p_2 = -78.54\\ \sigma_1 = -11.46 \quad \sigma_2 = -78.54 \]

Dermed er det et overdÃ¦mpet respons:

\[ K_1 \cdot e^{-\sigma_1 t} + K_2 \cdot e^{-\sigma_2 t} \]

Stepresponset bliver:

\[ A + K_1 \cdot e^{-11.46 t} + K_2 \cdot e^{-78.54 t} \]
